TEXT 496 -408 Left 2 ;Control signal frequency is 160 Hz\nFirst harmonic of voltage should be 160 Hz (Note current has 160 Hz and a ripple)\n \nFirst voltage harmonic amplitude of phase voltage is: V1 = ma Vd / 2 = (8/10)*(380) = 152V\nFirst harmonic voltage frequency is 160Hz\nFirst current harmonic amplitude is: I1 = V1/Z1 = 15 A\nWith Z1 = sqrt(1+(2pi*160*10mH)^2)\n \nLine to line voltage amplitude is V12 = sqrt(3)  ma Vd / 2 = sqrt(3)*(8/10)*(380) = 263 V
